        </div>
        <div class="column large-6 xlarge-5 xlarge-offset-1 learn-section-paragraphs">
          <p>Or maybe you already are a teacher? Or maybe you like your job, but believe in this mission? Or maybe you have a weird about-page fetish, and now you wanna take this to the next level? Whatever it may be, the least you can do is share the living crap out of this site, our animation, and anything else you find interesting, funny, or worthy of your precious social media channels.</p>
          <p>But maybe the best thing you could do is think really hard who you know, and who among them might make for a killer high school computer science teacher or grade school math teacher. Maybe your niece has a physics degree but no job, maybe your neighbor wants a career change, or maybe the person reading over your shoulder right now just really loves sharing and thus would make for a great teacher.</p>
          <p>Point is, these subjects are awesome. They’re mind blowing. And the opportunity to spread that knowledge is one of the most incredible opportunities afforded to not just our nation, but our species.</p>
          <p>Blow minds. Teach STEM. Read about pages.</p>
